<p>The <code>upper</code> function converts text to uppercase.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}'hello world' | upper{close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{'hello world' | upper}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}$sampleEmail | before('@') | upper{close}</pre>
<p>Username uppercase: <b>{$sampleEmail | before('@') | upper}</b></p>

<pre>{open}'  mixed CASE text  ' | trim | upper{close}</pre>
<p>Trim then uppercase: <b>{'  mixed CASE text  ' | trim | upper}</b></p>

<h2>Acronyms</h2>
<pre>{open}'application programming interface' | left(1){close}{open}'application programming interface' | after(' ') | left(1){close}{open}'application programming interface' | afterLast(' ') | left(1){close}</pre>
<p>Manual acronym: <b>{'application programming interface' | left(1) | upper}{'application programming interface' | after(' ') | left(1) | upper}{'application programming interface' | afterLast(' ') | left(1) | upper}</b></p>

<h2>With Users</h2>
<pre>{open}users{close}
  {open}$status | upper{close}: {open}$name{close}
{open}/users{close}</pre>
<p>Status badges:</p>
{users}
  <span style="background:#ddd;padding:2px 5px;">{$status | upper}</span> {$name}<br>
{/users}
